Teach them something.. Here’s how to do it:

Instagram users come to the platform to see something new. Ideally, they want to be WOW’d.

The growing popularity of hack videos or how-to tutorials continues to explode and rank as the top-performing videos on Instagram. 

Businesses and brands are starting to take notice too.

To get started.. Start thinking of things you can teach your audience.

For example, fitness brands can post how-to stretch videos before a run. The opportunities are endless.

The key is to make it centered around a common problem a customer of yours will face. 

The short video solves this problem by providing an easy-to-understand solution.

As consumers, we want the quick result delivered to us in a short, but informative way.

With video consumption on Instagram continually on the rise, consistent creation of new videos will drive traffic to your Instagram page for better engagement rates.

Get creative and start teaching!

Last year I met my mentor in London. If you met him on the street, you’d never think he was worth $800m. No flashy watch, no attitude, no brands on him, just humility all over his face. I told him I wanted to grow like him and he told me to offer services where the sky was the limit. He broke it down for me and said I needed 150 staff, managing 5 account each to become a billion dollar valued company. 9 months and 12 staff later, I can’t emphasise enough how much that helped me visualise growth. Yesterday, I met him again and I told him how scared I was with the fast pace of my business. He told me if everything is in order, it’s not right, but to always stay calm regardless. I’m sharing this story because it changed my life, and maybe it’ll change yours too 🙏🏽💛😊

My business strategy is crafted around this principle. Success is the dream, but how do you get there? What excites you to jolt out of bed to your first alarm and work on your goals? The thought of having [x] more followers? Sure, awesome. The freedom you'd have with more cash? Drooling! But the sense of PURPOSE you'd feel knowing people find value and meaning in your work is the real deal for me, and it happens to be the driving factor that will get you all of the above. 😍

Providing value is the BEST strategy for building an audience that knows and trusts you and your ideas. More than 80% of consumers consider TRUST a deciding factor in their buying decisions. Sadly, trust is in short supply in the world of advertising today, and I think we all have an inkling why. 

Times are changing - more people have access to creating media content. It's equally good news and bad. I'll start and end with the good: It provides an opportunity to stand out - to be better. And better = valuable 🤩

Provide authentic, specialized, and true value to your audience, and you will find yourself with an enthusiastic & trusting fanbase who can't wait to get their hands on your next offer.

How American Express Reached 15 Million People with Hashtags

American Express used a forward-thinking and creative approach to latch onto the popularity of Coachella to drive engagement for a brand awareness campaign. With the use of a hashtag.

#AmexAcess. Not only does a hashtag allow Instagram users to click and view all the photos shared with the hashtag. It also creates an easy-to-track method to gauge the campaign’s success.

The goal of the campaign? To drive awareness about new prizes and other features for American Express members who used their Amex information to register on the Coachella app.

Simple, right? But how did they do it?
Well, American Express was able to get high-level celebrities to post relevant photos using the #AmexAccess hashtag.

Brands have finally figured out how valued the dedicated audiences to celebrities are. Their influence is invaluable and shares on Instagram spread quicker than any other form of advertisement.

The campaign generated over 140,000 likes and 15 million unique views.

That’s 75 times more people than the average Coachella attendance. Not bad, right?

Build It and They Will Come

Over 500 million users on Instagram watch Stories every single day. This has created an entirely new way to get in front of your audience with native content.

In fact, 20% of all stories posted get at least one DM from viewers. 

Instagram engagement rates on stories are hard to ignore.

Stories can be used both for paid ads and organic content. And businesses are responsible for one-third of the most-viewed stories on the platform.

Some of the most popular ideas for Instagram stories for businesses include behind-the-scenes footage, product demos, and sales promotions. But it doesn’t stop there.

Instagram also provides interactive elements to include in your stories for better engagement. You can add stickers, polls, hashtags, or mentions to gain more attention.

Customer DM replies to a story could indicate strong brand loyalty, customer relationships, and buying intent. If your content was engaging enough to draw DM replies, be sure to reply in a timely manner.

Customers appreciate amazing response times and support above all else.

Use sound, video, and other interactive features to stand out.

Always be prepared to try new things and see what works for you!

How Airbnb Used Influencer Marketing to Reach 966 Million Users

It took Airbnb 12 years to go from a small startup to a 100 billion-dollar company. 

A large portion of this growth can be attributed to creative Instagram marketing campaigns.

Airbnb is quick to take notice of new trends. A perfect example of this is influencer marketing and its quick ability to incorporate it into their strategy.

The initiative began in late 2015. Here’s how they did it…

Mariah Carey was the first major celebrity to book a luxury Airbnb stay. The marketing team didn’t waste this opportunity. They were able to collaborate with Mariah for a sponsored IG post that garnered nearly 50,000 likes and comments.
The explosion in exposure opened up a new world for Airbnb.

Airbnb began sponsoring posts from key celebrities in exchange for luxury stays in Airbnbs. The goal was to reach a wider audience and change the perception of the company.
If you want luxury, choose Airbnb.
The strategy went even further to events when Lady Gaga posted a photo of her Airbnb in Houston at the Super Bowl.

Or when the likes of Wiz Khalifa and Drake did the same for Coachella.
It took 37 posts for Airbnb to reach a total of 966 million Instagram users in 2 years.

Tapping into other people’s audiences is a great way to achieve explosive growth.

1.Set specific, measurable goals: To effectively push yourself, you need to have clear goals in mind. Make sure your goals are specific and measurable, so you can track your progress and stay motivated.

2.Break big goals into smaller ones: If your goals seem daunting or overwhelming, try breaking them down into smaller, more manageable steps. This can help you avoid feeling discouraged or burnt out.

3.Celebrate your progress: It's important to acknowledge and celebrate the progress you make along the way, even if it's just small steps forward. Celebrating your progress can help you stay motivated and positive as you work towards your goals.

4.Listen to your body and mind: Pushing yourself too hard can lead to burnout or injury. Make sure you're taking care of yourself by getting enough rest, eating well, and giving yourself breaks when you need them.

5.Be flexible: Sometimes unexpected obstacles or challenges can arise on the path to reaching your goals. It's important to be flexible and adaptable, and to adjust your approach as needed to keep moving forward.

Reasons To Add Shea Butter To Your Routine 💅🏻

Shea butter is fat that’s extracted from the nuts of the shea tree. It’s solid at warm temperatures and has an off-white or ivory color. Shea butter has been used as a cosmetic ingredient for centuries. 

Curious? Here are 5 reasons to add it to your routine:

🧈 It's safe for all skin types
Shea butter doesn't contain chemical irritants known to dry out skin, and it doesn't clog pores. It's appropriate for nearly any skin type.

🧈 It won't make your skin oily
Shea butter is easy for your skin to fully absorb and won't make your skin look oily after application.

🧈 It offers added sun protection
Using shea butter on your skin does give you some added sun protection, so layer it over your favorite sunscreen on days you'll be spending outside.

🧈 It may help soothe sunburn and other skin burns
Shea's anti-inflammatory components may reduce redness and swelling. Its fatty acid components may also soothe the skin by retaining moisture during the healing process.

🧈 It may help prevent acne
Shea butter is rich in different kinds of fatty acids. This unique composition helps clear your skin of excess oil (sebum). The result is a restoration of the natural balance of oils in your skin, which may help stop acne before it starts.

Instagram vs. Competitors

With so many social media platforms, businesses struggle to pick one and try to focus on them all. This is an unsustainable strategy. Scattered efforts across the platforms will have you underperforming.

So what can you do?

The best decision is to pick one platform and go all in. Grow your brand here and after you gain traction, work outward and incorporate more social media into your business strategy.

We recommend Instagram. And it’s not even close.

The engagement rates on Instagram are 15 times higher than those on Facebook.

Considering Twitter? Instagram has engagement rates 20 times higher than them too.

The Instagram platform continues to evolve with new features that make it even easier to communicate with customers.

Photos and videos also reign supreme. It is a platform where consumers go to find new products and escape reality for a bit.

The businesses that can tell their own brand story creatively will win.

There has never been a better time to go all-in on your Instagram marketing than right now.

Когда речь заходит о целях все люди разделяются на две позиции, на так называемых «авторов», людей , которые готовы взять на себя ответственность и достичь поставленного результата и позиция жертвы , то есть по сути большинства людей. Это тот самый тип людей верящий, что обстоятельства выше или сильнее их, то что от них ничего не зависит или то, что нету другого выбора. 

На самом деле в достижении любой поставленной цели мышление играет колоссальную роль, около 85% и только оставшиеся 15% являются вашими твёрдыми навыками и умениям. 

Каждый раз перед постановкой новой цели , задумайтесь , зачем вам это нужно, верители вы в свой успех? Результат будет полностью зависеть от вашей преданности к поставленной цели.

The recent rally in Tesla stock is helping CEO Elon Musk close in on becoming the world's richest man once again.

Musk actually lost a bit of ground on Friday as Tesla shares fell 5% while US-listed shares of LVMH slipped just 1.1%, widening the wealth gap with Arnault by $3 billion from Thursday.

Everybody loves emojis. They lighten the mood and save time for typing and reading.

They work even better on Instagram. In fact, engagement increases by 48% on posts that use emojis to display their messages.

They attract eyeballs better on a cluttered feed and they help a brand feel more personable to people.

•Use emojis when replying to users in the comment section
•Use holiday themed emojis when necessary

If you aren’t sure, track your emoji posts with Instagram tools. Compare the engagement rates with posts that don’t use emojis and see the results.
Emojis are a way to lighten the mood in text messaging. For brands, it is a way to humanize the business and relate to their customers better.

The most liked picture on Instagram is an egg

Yes. A plain egg. The egg photo collected over 25 million likes.

There is even a profile dedicated to this egg with over 5 million followers. So why does this matter?

This is a perfect example of taking something simple and making it a viral phenomenon. The original goal of the egg photo was to surpass Kylie Jenner as the most liked photo. Mission accomplished.

Word of mouth and the reach of Instagram is extremely powerful.
Set goals for all of your Instagram campaigns. They don't have to be as ambitious as the egg post, but staying aligned with your goals will assure you are posting quality content.

Keep it simple. Talk to your audience.
It won’t always be perfect but adjusting based on your audience is the best strategy to keep building upwards.

Now go make your page Eggcellent!

1️⃣ Knowledge is power, I try to read a chapter of nonfiction a day or listen to a podcast epidsode.
2️⃣ Freckles, dry skin, and overgrown bangs. I prefer taking selfies when I’m tired. It feels more honest.
3️⃣ Streamlining my side hustles. I currently have 3 websites in the pipeline—a yoga blog, a writing portfolio, and a passion project. Stay tuned!

🧡As we celebrate Random Acts of Kindness Day on February 17th, 2023, let us take a moment to reflect on the power of kindness and the impact it has on others.

Kindness is a simple but powerful gesture that can make someone's day a little brighter. It doesn't have to be a grand gesture - even small acts of kindness can go a long way in making someone feel seen and appreciated. Whether it's holding the door open for someone, offering a compliment, or simply smiling at a stranger, these little acts of kindness can create a ripple effect of positivity that can spread far beyond just one person🎁

On this day, let's challenge ourselves to spread kindness and compassion wherever we go. Let's take the time to be present and thoughtful with those around us, and show them that we care. Whether it's a friend, a family member, or a stranger, a small act of kindness can make all the difference in someone's day🥰

Remember, kindness is contagious. By spreading kindness and positivity, we can create a ripple effect that can touch countless lives. So, let's make Random Acts of Kindness Day 2023 a day to remember, and commit to spreading love, kindness, and compassion in our daily lives. Together, we can make the world a better place, one act of kindness at a time. #kindness

Tak terbantahkan perusahaan logistic dan cargo pun berdampak krisis akibat dengan pandemi COVID-19. David Belen, selaku pemilik PT. David Bali Cargotama berupaya mencari celah positif dan enggan memandang secara keseluruhan wabah ini dengan tatapan sinis. Harus tetap bertahan, bahkan tetap abundance dalam segala hal, kesehatan, materi dan kreatifitas.

David Bali Cargotama yang telah beroperasi sejak Maret 2016, memang sudah tak diragukan lagi jam terbangnya, terlebih saat dipertanyakan soal strategi mempertahankan bisnis dalam masa pandemi. Dinahkodai David Belen, pria asal Kupang, Nusa Tenggara Timur ini mengungkapkan dengan sigap, ia wajib menciptakan produk baru dan memperluas pangsa-pangsa pasar, tak hanya kaku menghandle cargo-cargo untuk barang komersil saja, karena kondisi penurunan kunjungan wisatawan, otomatis tak ada kegiatan pembelanjaan, cargo pun ikut-ikutan sepi.

David pun merambah layanan pengangkutan untuk tren pembelanjaan secara daring; masuk asosiasi mobil antik dalam pengiriman kendaraan; merelokasi barang-barang yang bersifat pribadi ke luar negeri, selain secara door to door termasuk semua dokumen yang diperlukan, bea cukai kedua negara. Proses relokasi pun lebih mudah, aman dan membebaskan klien dari situasi rumit. Jangkauan klien pun meluas, meliputi klien pemerintah, bidang medis dan profesi diplomat. Berlanjut, David juga memperluas pangsa pasar dengan menambahkan perizinan perusahaannya tidak sebatas bidang transportasi semata, akan tetapi melakukan trading export-import komoditi non migas yang membeli berbagai produk supplier untuk dijual kembali ke pasar internasional demi membantu ekonomi Bali tetap berjalan dimasa pandemi kemarin.

Dropshipping 101: Fulfillment 🔥

When an order comes in, it's time to fulfill it! As a dropshipper, you don't have to worry about inventory or shipping, but you still need to make sure your customers get their orders on time. Here's how it works:

1️⃣ You receive an order on your store
2️⃣ You forward the order to your supplier
3️⃣ The supplier ships the product directly to your customer
4️⃣ You notify the customer that their order is on the way

That's it! With dropshipping, fulfillment is fast and easy. No need to handle any physical products yourself.

.

Biznes? Słyszałem o jednym takim co „próbował” i mu nie wyszło, a potem każdy o nim gadał. Jakieś piramidy czy inne syfy - w telewizji gadali i w internecie czytałem - czyli w dwóch wiarygodnych źródłach informacji. .
Zarabianie przez internet? Jeszcze mnie oszukają, spotkania przed komputerem, wspólne szkolenia, wyjazdy, wakacje - co za bajki, nie widzą jakie ciężkie jest życie. PIS teraz mówił, że przedsiębiorcy maja płacić dużo zusu. Szkoda zachodu..
.

caption:
Sharing is caring

Share for share has become a popular way for influencers and businesses to expand their reach without spending money on advertising.

It’s a simple process.

Two parties agree to both share a piece of content on behalf of the other on their page. It can be done with a story post or an actual post on their feed.

It serves as a way to engage with your audience in a new way while getting in front of a new audience that might be interested in you too.

If this interests you, start by finding people in the niche you want to target.

Send them a personalized DM and explain your intentions. It would be helpful to give them a description of your audience too so they can see the benefit right away.

The key is to use a call-to-action post so any potential viewers will know where to find you and what to do when they find you. That could be a follow, sign up for your newsletter, buy a product, etc.

The worst that can happen is you gain a new Instagram alley. Give it a shot!

A digital asset is a digital representation of value which is recorded on a cryptographically secured, distributed ledger. Common digital assets include:

👉 Convertible virtual currency and cryptocurrency
👉 Stablecoins
👉 Non-fungible tokens (NFTs)

‼ The IRS reminded taxpayers that they must again answer a digital asset question and report all digital asset-related income when they file their 2022 federal income tax return, as they did for fiscal year 2021. The term "digital assets" has replaced "virtual currencies," a term used in previous years.

📑 The question, which appears at the top of Forms 1040, Individual Income Tax Return; 1040-SR, U.S. Tax Return for Seniors; and 1040-NR, U.S. Nonresident Alien Income Tax Return, was revised this year to update terminology.

💡 In addition, the instructions for answering the question were expanded and clarified to help taxpayers answer it correctly. All taxpayers must answer the question regardless of whether they engaged in any transactions involving digital assets.

How to sell on Instagram

Customers like to be sold. Only when they don’t realize it. Selling naturally is a gift.

Start by teasing followers with upcoming announcements. Before the product drops, show them a post with details about the drop to build up the excitement for the product.

Create a sense of urgency on posts to push customers closer to buying. 

Announce a window of time for a sale to be used.

Use words like “now” in your Call To Actions too. Reading “Call now” is more enticing than “Call anytime.

Add contact buttons in your profile too. Instagram allows business profiles to add quick use buttons to email or call a business directly from the app. Take advantage.

By using sales words in your posts, customers are being sold without realizing it. If the content is good enough, they’ll want to join you anyways.

Always be sure to tie it in nicely with the photo too. The best Instagram execution is natively adjusting to the platform.

Get out there and make some sales!

Are you taking advantage of the data?

You wouldn’t dare bake a cake without measuring the right amount of flour...right?

Then there is no way you should be running social media promotions without tracking the data too. That’s crazy!

Instagram doesn’t have an in-depth analytics platform built in like Facebook. We must rely on third party tools. Luckily, there are some great ones.

Iconosquare allows businesses to link their profiles and get a deep look into how users are interacting with their business.

Track your key metrics accurately in once place. You will have instant access to profile, individual post, and story analytics to see what is working and what isn't working.

The best way to improve content is by doubling down on what is working the best. Iconosquare even has a feature that lets you breakdown your mentions and comments. 

See which comments are doing the best and who is mentioning you where.

As an added bonus, they have post scheduling features too.

Stay on top of your analytics for the best results!
